Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF) cathode perovskite prepared by a Pechini method deposited on ceria co-doping Ce(0.8)Sm(0.17)Ln(0.03)O(1.9) (LnSDC), with (Ln = La, Y, and Nd) electrolytes was successfully prepared by the solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In this preparation process, thick and thin films of LSCF were deposited upon dense Ln-doped ceria LnSDC electrolytes after 5 and 3 spin-coating and dip-coating cycles, respectively.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Two layers of LSCF were deposited by screen-printing in order to obtain thick cathode films.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: After deposition, some structural and morphologic characterizations, such as X-ray diffraction analysis and scanning electron microscopy, have been conducted to understand the properties of the elaborated samples and to study the impact of doping on these properties.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements on symmetric cells were also performed to investigate the employability of L0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta as a cathode material deposited upon LnSDC electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: According to what was available and inferred after studying the images from a scanning electron microscope, no cracks or significant segregation were detected in the LSCF/LnSDC interface.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: This behavior is consistent with the good thermal expansion compatibility between the two materials.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy investigations at 700 degrees C, indicate relatively low area-specific resistance between 0.048 and 0.1 ohm cm(2) for all symmetrical cell LSCF/doped electrolyte/LSCF.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: All the cells were previously sintered above 1400 degrees C, in air.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: All these results showed that L0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3- delta can stand as a potential candidate for new cathode material in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Cathode Performance Study of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ with Various Electrolyte-Doped Ceria Ce0.8Sm0.17Ln0.03O1.9 for IT-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
